Comment: Hi @jodenda :-) !

I agree with your funny Contribution (and humor in Test cases :-) :+1: !

I've just a suggestion for you : in your Statements, you says "Proteins are made up of 20 amino acids"
and in your Constraints, you says length <= 30 ...
-> maybe you can add some Test cases (& Validator) with 19 or 20 letters (could be / or not a Protein)
-> and at least 1 Test (& Validator) with 21 letters => not a Protein, but maybe DNA or RNA ?

Here my C# to handle my suggestion ;-) :
        const string DNA = "ATGC";
        const string RNA = "AUGC";
        const string Protein = "ACDEFGHIKLMNPQRSTVWY";
        string SEQUENCE = Console.ReadLine();
        Console.Error.WriteLine(SEQUENCE + " is " + SEQUENCE.Length.ToString());
        bool isDna = SEQUENCE.All(c => DNA.Contains(c));
        bool isRNA = SEQUENCE.All(c => RNA.Contains(c));
        bool isProt = (SEQUENCE.Length <= 20) && SEQUENCE.All(c => Protein.Contains(c));
        string ans = "";
        if(isDna) ans += (ans.Length > 0 ? " or " : "") +  "DNA";
        if(isRNA) ans += (ans.Length > 0 ? " or " : "") +  "RNA";
        if(isProt) ans += (ans.Length > 0 ? " or " : "") +  "Protein";
        if(ans.Length <= 0) ans = "artificial";
        Console.WriteLine(SEQUENCE + " is " + ans);
